62
00:04:37,380 --> 00:04:41,140
♪As you nap
on my shoulder in the afternoon♪

63
00:04:42,590 --> 00:04:44,230
(I'd like to have a garden)

64
00:04:45,180 --> 00:04:47,710
(where I can grow vegetables)

65
00:04:48,350 --> 00:04:49,670
(and flowers.)

66
00:04:51,110 --> 00:04:52,710
(And I'd like to have a)

67
00:04:53,110 --> 00:04:54,990
(puppy like Xiaodi.)

68
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:57,560
(And I want)

69
00:04:58,060 --> 00:05:00,420
(a big fridge.)

70
00:05:01,030 --> 00:05:03,180
The fridge is full

71
00:05:03,740 --> 00:05:06,060
(of fridge magnets of all the places)

72
00:05:06,060 --> 00:05:06,990
(we've been.)

73
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:08,780
♪Pain♪

74
00:05:09,060 --> 00:05:12,620
♪Life troubles me year after year♪

75
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:14,350
I also want

76
00:05:16,350 --> 00:05:18,940
a kitchen...

77
00:05:21,030 --> 00:05:22,180
The kitchen is...

78
00:05:22,380 --> 00:05:25,020
♪But the sky is clear♪

79
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:29,540
♪Hope shines
like light across the prairie♪

80
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:33,100
♪Your kindness♪

81
00:05:33,420 --> 00:05:38,018
♪I long for it,
yet the wind chills me again♪

82
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:59,020
♪Give me a brief taste of sweetness♪

83
00:05:59,460 --> 00:06:03,300
♪May our love last long♪

84
00:06:04,020 --> 00:06:06,100
♪My baby♪

85
00:06:08,140 --> 00:06:10,300
♪My baby♪

86
00:06:12,260 --> 00:06:15,540
♪I think of you in my mad dash♪

87
00:06:15,900 --> 00:06:19,740
♪My daze of boredom
is also about you♪

88
00:06:20,540 --> 00:06:22,460
♪My baby♪

89
00:06:22,740 --> 00:06:23,710
You're all

90
00:06:25,940 --> 00:06:26,620
I need.

91
00:06:58,820 --> 00:06:59,710
Let's learn this today.

92
00:07:01,733 --> 00:07:03,790
(Advanced Math,
Linear Algebra for Engineering Math)

93
00:07:03,790 --> 00:07:04,300
These

94
00:07:05,030 --> 00:07:06,230
are university courses.

95
00:07:07,311 --> 00:07:08,420
I'm done with high school,

96
00:07:08,533 --> 00:07:09,977
so I'll advance to university.

97
00:07:12,940 --> 00:07:13,740
Actually,

98
00:07:14,380 --> 00:07:15,740
you don't need to learn this now.

99
00:07:15,990 --> 00:07:16,590
No,

100
00:07:16,790 --> 00:07:17,590
I have to learn.

101
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,230
There are other students in our class

102
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:20,260
who are learning too.

103
00:07:23,820 --> 00:07:24,260
Why do you

104
00:07:24,260 --> 00:07:25,977
have to compare yourself with others?

105
00:07:27,155 --> 00:07:29,155
I can't accept that others
are better than me.

106
00:07:29,230 --> 00:07:30,422
I just want to be number one.

107
00:07:33,844 --> 00:07:35,466
Why do you just want to be number one?

108
00:07:36,710 --> 00:07:37,350
I have no idea.

109
00:07:38,470 --> 00:07:39,710
I'm just used to being first.

110
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:41,030
You've never been second?

111
00:07:41,620 --> 00:07:42,150
No.

112
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:47,260
You're a lot

113
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:47,990
like the old me.

114
00:07:48,940 --> 00:07:49,710
The old you?

115
00:07:53,088 --> 00:07:54,500
From primary school to high school,

116
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:55,620
I never came second.

117
00:07:58,590 --> 00:07:59,300
At that time,

118
00:07:59,733 --> 00:08:01,520
I was a genius in the eyes
of both students

119
00:08:01,550 --> 00:08:02,380
and parents.

120
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,688
Studying gave me a sense
of achievement.

121
00:08:06,990 --> 00:08:07,990
As time went by,

122
00:08:08,060 --> 00:08:09,110
I felt

123
00:08:10,060 --> 00:08:11,590
I was born to be better than others.

124
00:08:12,866 --> 00:08:14,550
But then I went to Yenching University

125
00:08:15,350 --> 00:08:16,230
and I realized

126
00:08:18,470 --> 00:08:19,710
that it wasn't like that at all.

127
00:08:20,260 --> 00:08:22,550
Because you couldn't easily
be number one anymore?

128
00:08:26,260 --> 00:08:27,620
That was the first time I found

129
00:08:28,790 --> 00:08:30,380
studying to be painful.

130
00:08:35,950 --> 00:08:36,430
(Then, I)

131
00:08:36,470 --> 00:08:37,590
(studied day and night.)

132
00:08:40,511 --> 00:08:41,470
(Finally, on one exam,)

133
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:42,310
(I came in second.)

134
00:08:43,590 --> 00:08:44,230
(That's good.)

135
00:08:44,266 --> 00:08:45,190
(You can be number one)

136
00:08:45,190 --> 00:08:45,860
(after that.)

137
00:08:48,260 --> 00:08:48,900
(I gave up.)

138
00:08:51,140 --> 00:08:51,830
Why?

139
00:08:53,540 --> 00:08:54,830
Because I found out

140
00:08:55,950 --> 00:08:57,710
that the top student in our class

141
00:08:59,022 --> 00:09:02,230
is a 15-year-old kid
who doesn't usually come to class.

142
00:09:03,830 --> 00:09:04,660
A whiz-kid?

143
00:09:07,341 --> 00:09:10,620
(End-of-term Results for Clinical
Medicine, Professional Ranking 2)

144
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:23,220
(Professional Ranking 2)

145
00:09:23,470 --> 00:09:24,740
(That was the moment)

146
00:09:25,230 --> 00:09:26,260
(I realized)

147
00:09:27,555 --> 00:09:31,350
(that a lot of things
I had to work very hard for)

148
00:09:31,860 --> 00:09:33,140
(were as easy as drinking water)

149
00:09:33,430 --> 00:09:34,950
(for some people.)

150
00:09:36,380 --> 00:09:37,710
From that moment on,

151
00:09:38,900 --> 00:09:39,590
I gave up

152
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:41,244
my obsession with being number one

153
00:09:41,540 --> 00:09:43,350
and accepted the fact

154
00:09:43,830 --> 00:09:44,470
that I was just

155
00:09:45,070 --> 00:09:46,380
an ordinary person.

156
00:09:48,590 --> 00:09:49,900
Are you happy now?

157
00:09:53,860 --> 00:09:55,140
All I can say is

158
00:09:55,688 --> 00:09:57,070
that I'm a lot more relaxed.

159
00:10:24,020 --> 00:10:25,310
Song Cong, wait a minute.

160
00:10:31,377 --> 00:10:33,266
Here's the last tuition
for makeup lessons.

161
00:10:33,590 --> 00:10:35,990
They asked for a new teacher.

162
00:10:38,590 --> 00:10:39,230
Thank you.

163
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,020
Sorry to trouble you.

164
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:42,380
Aren't you surprised?

165
00:10:43,470 --> 00:10:44,350
I could guess.

166
00:10:45,230 --> 00:10:46,710
Can I ask why?

167
00:10:46,866 --> 00:10:48,933
It's certainly not a matter
of professionalism.

168
00:10:49,020 --> 00:10:50,740
If you can't teach them,

169
00:10:51,310 --> 00:10:53,020
I don't know who to recommend.

170
00:10:54,260 --> 00:10:55,230
I probably

171
00:10:55,830 --> 00:10:57,470
can't satisfy their demands.

172
00:10:58,620 --> 00:11:00,140
He wants to be number one forever,

173
00:11:01,430 --> 00:11:02,860
but who can be number one forever?

174
00:11:08,266 --> 00:11:09,540
I'm sorry for the trouble.

175
00:11:11,020 --> 00:11:11,900
Let me buy you a meal.

176
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,380
It's payday.

177
00:11:13,710 --> 00:11:14,430
I'm buying.

178
00:11:15,380 --> 00:11:15,830
Okay.

179
00:11:24,860 --> 00:11:26,310
I told you I'd buy you a meal.

180
00:11:26,444 --> 00:11:28,140
Why don't you let me
buy you a nice meal?

181
00:11:28,950 --> 00:11:30,070
I think this is nice.

182
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:31,740
There's no need for formality.

183
00:11:34,230 --> 00:11:34,860
Actually, you...

184
00:11:35,310 --> 00:11:37,110
You didn't have to talk so much
to that kid.

185
00:11:37,990 --> 00:11:39,590
If you hadn't talked
to him about life,

186
00:11:39,780 --> 00:11:41,260
you wouldn't have lost your job.

187
00:11:46,070 --> 00:11:47,020
I saw him

188
00:11:47,716 --> 00:11:49,076
and thought of my old self.

189
00:11:50,260 --> 00:11:52,590
I was also afraid
that he'd lose his self-confidence

190
00:11:52,590 --> 00:11:53,755
if he entered an environment

191
00:11:53,777 --> 00:11:55,088
like Yenching University.

192
00:11:58,133 --> 00:11:59,380
But there are some things

193
00:11:59,430 --> 00:12:00,620
you can't understand

194
00:12:00,644 --> 00:12:02,155
until you've experienced them yourself.

195
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:05,590
I remember

196
00:12:05,866 --> 00:12:08,260
you were always in the top three
in high school, right?

197
00:12:08,710 --> 00:12:10,020
How did you adjust your mindset?

198
00:12:10,950 --> 00:12:11,540
Do you know

199
00:12:11,540 --> 00:12:13,377
how much I wanted to be number one?

200
00:12:14,860 --> 00:12:15,990
But as long as you're around,

201
00:12:16,230 --> 00:12:17,140
I'd never get it.

202
00:12:18,710 --> 00:12:19,740
So, thanks to you,

203
00:12:20,140 --> 00:12:21,140
I'm used to it.

204
00:12:23,350 --> 00:12:24,590
Shouldn't you thank me?

205
00:12:25,860 --> 00:12:27,310
I found you a job.

206
00:12:31,470 --> 00:12:32,780
And I grew up knowing

207
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:34,620
that I don't always get

208
00:12:34,620 --> 00:12:35,740
what I want.

209
00:12:38,333 --> 00:12:39,590
This dish is quite tasty.

210
00:12:44,020 --> 00:12:44,710
Eat more.

211
00:12:52,710 --> 00:12:54,020
Hello, guys.

212
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:55,070
You're here.

213
00:12:55,070 --> 00:12:56,019
What took you so long?

214
00:12:56,020 --> 00:12:56,590
Sorry,

215
00:12:56,590 --> 00:12:57,110
we're late.

216
00:12:57,266 --> 00:12:58,350
You have no sense of time.

217
00:12:58,350 --> 00:13:00,190
It's only five minutes late, Xinyan.

218
00:13:00,311 --> 00:13:01,400
Did you order the food?

219
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:03,680
Yes. I thought I'd wait for you
before they serve the food.

220
00:13:03,688 --> 00:13:04,800
Start with some appetizers.

221
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:05,222
Sure.

222
00:13:05,244 --> 00:13:05,733
Okay.

223
00:13:07,110 --> 00:13:07,590
Huan'er,

224
00:13:08,020 --> 00:13:09,070
you and Jing Xichi

225
00:13:09,140 --> 00:13:10,511
will stay in Wu'an from now on?

226
00:13:10,540 --> 00:13:11,590
Highly probable.

227
00:13:11,866 --> 00:13:14,177
I applied for graduate school
at my school.

228
00:13:14,244 --> 00:13:15,430
He's handed over his person

229
00:13:15,950 --> 00:13:17,190
and his website

230
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:18,310
to the company.

231
00:13:18,540 --> 00:13:19,830
He'll be working for them.

232
00:13:20,740 --> 00:13:21,900
Not bad, Jing Xichi.

233
00:13:21,990 --> 00:13:23,190
Whether or not

234
00:13:23,310 --> 00:13:25,310
the next Bill Gates
or Zuckerberg appears

235
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:28,070
in my circle depends on you.

236
00:13:28,260 --> 00:13:29,066
I'll try my best.

237
00:13:29,830 --> 00:13:31,110
Do well in university.

238
00:13:31,133 --> 00:13:32,190
Don't think of dropping out.

239
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:32,955
Of course not.

240
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:35,140
Time flies.

241
00:13:35,590 --> 00:13:37,710
A rebellious teenager
becomes a henpecked man.

242
00:13:39,620 --> 00:13:40,620
Who says otherwise?

243
00:13:41,260 --> 00:13:42,710
You two are better.

244
00:13:42,777 --> 00:13:45,266
Pursuing master's
and doctoral degrees consecutively.

245
00:13:45,266 --> 00:13:46,688
You've seen the pigs getting fed,

246
00:13:46,733 --> 00:13:48,266
but not them getting slaughtered.

247
00:13:48,350 --> 00:13:49,900
I wish I could have graduated earlier.

248
00:13:50,380 --> 00:13:51,500
Hello, everyone!

249
00:13:51,620 --> 00:13:52,710
You're so late.

250
00:13:52,860 --> 00:13:53,780
You're finally here.

251
00:13:56,310 --> 00:13:58,260
Isn't this Mr. Li?

252
00:13:58,260 --> 00:14:00,440
I heard you're going back
to Tianhe No.3 Central Hospital

253
00:14:00,444 --> 00:14:01,240
for your internship.

254
00:14:01,310 --> 00:14:02,350
Yes, that's the plan.

255
00:14:02,900 --> 00:14:04,310
You're the most obedient.

256
00:14:04,590 --> 00:14:05,140
What's wrong?

257
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:06,110
He's doing good.

258
00:14:06,230 --> 00:14:07,620
He lives and eats at home,

259
00:14:07,830 --> 00:14:09,488
and his immediate superior is his dad.

260
00:14:09,710 --> 00:14:10,350
Unlike us,

261
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:12,620
we work hard every day for our future.

262
00:14:13,140 --> 00:14:14,020
He's lying

263
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:15,430
on the finish line now.

264
00:14:15,780 --> 00:14:16,740
He's a life winner.

265
00:14:17,190 --> 00:14:17,900
Don't say that.

266
00:14:17,990 --> 00:14:19,190
A life winner?

267
00:14:19,350 --> 00:14:20,380
I haven't even had

268
00:14:20,430 --> 00:14:21,470
a girlfriend.

269
00:14:23,740 --> 00:14:25,620
Liao Xinyan, stop chatting on the phone.

270
00:14:25,620 --> 00:14:26,860
It's a class reunion.

271
00:14:26,888 --> 00:14:28,288
You can chat until you get home.

272
00:14:28,355 --> 00:14:29,350
He's clingy.

273
00:14:30,950 --> 00:14:31,860
No, no.

274
00:14:32,350 --> 00:14:33,070
I suspect

275
00:14:33,110 --> 00:14:34,110
my recent toothache

276
00:14:34,190 --> 00:14:35,355
must be due to seeing too many

277
00:14:35,377 --> 00:14:36,577
of your affectionate displays.

278
00:14:36,577 --> 00:14:37,155
Pissed me off.

279
00:14:37,260 --> 00:14:38,780
What? You want to fall in love?

280
00:14:39,110 --> 00:14:39,710
You don't?

281
00:14:39,830 --> 00:14:40,540
I don't.

282
00:14:41,710 --> 00:14:43,740
You and Song go to the same university.

283
00:14:43,844 --> 00:14:45,355
Why don't you two try to fall in love?

284
00:14:45,355 --> 00:14:46,710
Why are you still such a talker?

285
00:14:47,230 --> 00:14:47,900
What's wrong?

286
00:14:48,140 --> 00:14:49,230
If you criticize me again,

287
00:14:49,310 --> 00:14:51,110
I'll sing the alphabet song
for everyone.

288
00:14:51,660 --> 00:14:52,555
What alphabet song?

289
00:14:52,780 --> 00:14:54,740
A, B, C, D...

290
00:14:54,740 --> 00:14:55,190
Come here.

291
00:14:55,230 --> 00:14:56,020
E, F, G.

292
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:56,577
Keep singing.

293
00:14:56,577 --> 00:14:57,020
What?

294
00:14:57,044 --> 00:14:57,955
You still want to sing?

295
00:14:58,020 --> 00:14:58,620
Don't touch me!

296
00:14:58,644 --> 00:14:59,555
Are you singing or not?

297
00:14:59,660 --> 00:15:01,070
Sing loudly. Come on.

298
00:15:01,070 --> 00:15:01,620
Come in.

299
00:15:03,070 --> 00:15:03,780
Hi,

300
00:15:04,020 --> 00:15:05,860
we got a call from a Mr. Bai.

301
00:15:05,950 --> 00:15:06,780
He asked us

302
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:08,310
to give this to Ms. Liao Xinyan.

303
00:15:11,380 --> 00:15:13,350
My tooth hurts even more.

304
00:15:13,780 --> 00:15:15,310
It's been almost two and a half years.

305
00:15:15,380 --> 00:15:16,710
Why is he still so sweet?

306
00:15:17,070 --> 00:15:17,900
What?

307
00:15:18,190 --> 00:15:19,540
Singles don't get to talk,

308
00:15:19,590 --> 00:15:20,070
huh?

309
00:15:20,590 --> 00:15:22,780
The one she's chatting with isn't this.

310
00:15:26,420 --> 00:15:28,580
(My baby, I don't want
to break up with you)

311
00:15:34,430 --> 00:15:36,020
No wonder they say

312
00:15:36,110 --> 00:15:37,780
graduation season is break-up season.

313
00:15:38,350 --> 00:15:39,190
Anyway, Xinyan,

314
00:15:39,950 --> 00:15:41,780
we're in the second half
of our third year.

315
00:15:42,070 --> 00:15:43,710
Isn't it a bit early for you

316
00:15:44,070 --> 00:15:44,860
to break up?

317
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:51,190
I... I'm really fine.

318
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:54,733
I just want to graduate and take
the civil service exam back to Tianhe.

319
00:15:54,780 --> 00:15:55,710
He's an only child.

320
00:15:56,155 --> 00:15:57,380
His home is near our school,

321
00:15:57,380 --> 00:15:58,511
and I can't come back.

322
00:15:58,710 --> 00:15:59,500
I thought

323
00:15:59,540 --> 00:16:01,190
I'd let go and be free.

324
00:16:01,430 --> 00:16:03,070
I'm looking for my next romance.

325
00:16:05,900 --> 00:16:07,260
If that's the case,

326
00:16:07,511 --> 00:16:09,710
we'll wish you good luck
on your civil service exam.

327
00:16:09,830 --> 00:16:10,190
Okay?

328
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:10,900
Sure.

329
00:16:11,020 --> 00:16:11,430
Come on.

330
00:16:11,540 --> 00:16:11,950
Wait.

331
00:16:11,990 --> 00:16:13,620
We're drinking

332
00:16:13,710 --> 00:16:14,844
before the food is served?

333
00:16:15,310 --> 00:16:15,950
Jing Xichi,

334
00:16:16,140 --> 00:16:17,990
we didn't decide
on a winner last time, did we?

335
00:16:18,140 --> 00:16:18,620
Come on.

336
00:16:18,900 --> 00:16:19,430
This time,

337
00:16:19,540 --> 00:16:20,777
do you want to fight me again?

338
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:21,740
Put that drink down.

339
00:16:21,780 --> 00:16:23,070
You can't get drunk today,

340
00:16:23,140 --> 00:16:24,470
even if everyone else does.

341
00:16:25,380 --> 00:16:26,990
Then let's cut the cake

342
00:16:27,070 --> 00:16:29,260
to celebrate my happy breakup.

343
00:16:29,377 --> 00:16:29,990
Cut the cake.

344
00:16:30,110 --> 00:16:30,780
Come on.

345
00:16:31,110 --> 00:16:31,900
Waitress.

346
00:16:32,710 --> 00:16:33,190
Knife.

347
00:16:33,590 --> 00:16:33,990
Knife.

348
00:16:34,020 --> 00:16:34,577
I'll get her.

349
00:16:34,644 --> 00:16:35,380
Miss.

350
00:16:35,590 --> 00:16:36,260
What do you need?

351
00:16:36,310 --> 00:16:36,990
Knife.

352
00:16:37,990 --> 00:16:38,620
Waitress.

353
00:16:38,620 --> 00:16:39,740
Here it is.

354
00:16:40,590 --> 00:16:42,229
The knife is here.

355
00:16:42,355 --> 00:16:43,555
I'm so speechless of you.

356
00:16:43,866 --> 00:16:45,430
Xinyan, you're making a fool of us...

357
00:16:45,430 --> 00:16:46,020
Be careful.

358
00:16:46,540 --> 00:16:47,620
Cut the ties of love.

359
00:16:48,260 --> 00:16:49,830
This knife is so big.

360
00:16:50,660 --> 00:16:52,190
But I really didn't expect

361
00:16:52,350 --> 00:16:53,900
Xinyan to take the civil service exam.

362
00:16:54,990 --> 00:16:57,140
Maybe she's the one who knows

363
00:16:57,310 --> 00:16:59,230
what she wants the most among us.

364
00:17:00,470 --> 00:17:01,070
Jing Xichi,

365
00:17:01,470 --> 00:17:03,350
do you think we'll change?

366
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:06,870
No matter how you change,

367
00:17:07,260 --> 00:17:08,470
my love for you

368
00:17:08,844 --> 00:17:09,580
will never change.

369
00:17:10,020 --> 00:17:11,260
Be serious.

370
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:12,044
I'll go back now.

371
00:17:12,088 --> 00:17:13,190
I'm very serious.

372
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:15,777
You're just leaving like that.

373
00:17:16,022 --> 00:17:16,933
Where is my kiss?

374
00:17:17,950 --> 00:17:18,710
Stop it.

375
00:17:18,780 --> 00:17:19,990
What if my dad sees it?

376
00:17:20,293 --> 00:17:21,573
There's no one here.

377
00:17:22,060 --> 00:17:22,580
Don't.

378
00:17:25,390 --> 00:17:26,300
Your dad already knew.

379
00:17:26,333 --> 00:17:27,222
What are you afraid of?

380
00:17:27,222 --> 00:17:27,911
Don't be late.

381
00:17:27,950 --> 00:17:28,430
I'm leaving.

382
00:17:28,430 --> 00:17:28,910
Go back now.

383
00:17:29,430 --> 00:17:30,230
Get up early.

384
00:17:30,910 --> 00:17:31,630
Got it.

385
00:17:32,630 --> 00:17:35,100
(Second semester of third year)

386
00:17:35,260 --> 00:17:36,311
(arrives in a rush.)

387
00:17:36,670 --> 00:17:38,710
(Youth comes to a screeching halt)

388
00:17:38,740 --> 00:17:39,740
(when it stumbles.)

389
00:17:40,740 --> 00:17:42,340
(The note of parting is played.)

390
00:17:42,910 --> 00:17:43,990
(We've reached)

391
00:17:44,260 --> 00:17:46,430
(the point where we're facing society
and the future.)

392
00:17:46,950 --> 00:17:47,950
(But life)

393
00:17:48,340 --> 00:17:50,020
(is always full of surprises.)

394
00:17:50,340 --> 00:17:51,390
I'll raise a toast.

395
00:17:55,244 --> 00:17:57,022
There's a message from the counselor.

396
00:17:57,950 --> 00:17:58,580
Let me see.

397
00:18:02,355 --> 00:18:03,470
It's this late in the day

398
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:04,630
and he's still sending out

399
00:18:04,644 --> 00:18:05,844
internship questionnaires.

400
00:18:05,844 --> 00:18:07,020
The third year isn't over yet,

401
00:18:07,020 --> 00:18:09,000
and we're already looking forward
to the future.

402
00:18:10,580 --> 00:18:11,020
Right,

403
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:11,780
Lu,

404
00:18:11,780 --> 00:18:12,500
I thought you said

405
00:18:12,540 --> 00:18:14,133
you were looking for a job in advance.

406
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:14,950
How is it?

407
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:17,580
I've been thinking about it,

408
00:18:18,300 --> 00:18:20,230
and I've got maybe
30 or 40 years of time

409
00:18:20,260 --> 00:18:21,820
to work in the future.

410
00:18:22,150 --> 00:18:22,780
But I only have

411
00:18:22,820 --> 00:18:24,260
a year or so left to fall in love

412
00:18:24,300 --> 00:18:25,710
in university.

413
00:18:26,100 --> 00:18:27,430
So I've decided

414
00:18:27,430 --> 00:18:28,710
not to rush into finding a job.

415
00:18:28,950 --> 00:18:30,500
I'm going to have

416
00:18:30,580 --> 00:18:31,910
a good love affair

417
00:18:32,060 --> 00:18:33,670
in university.

418
00:18:34,100 --> 00:18:34,950
To be honest,

419
00:18:35,020 --> 00:18:36,190
what are your plans?

420
00:18:36,580 --> 00:18:37,710
It's senior year.

421
00:18:37,740 --> 00:18:39,230
It's the norm for couples to break up

422
00:18:39,300 --> 00:18:40,600
and go their separate ways.

423
00:18:40,710 --> 00:18:41,260
Huan'er,

424
00:18:41,300 --> 00:18:42,444
you've got to be careful.

425
00:18:43,260 --> 00:18:44,580
Jing Xichi's work

426
00:18:44,710 --> 00:18:45,580
is on track now.

427
00:18:45,950 --> 00:18:48,260
I think I'll stay in Wu'an too.

428
00:18:48,622 --> 00:18:50,022
You're going to graduate school?

429
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:50,910
I can't help it.

430
00:18:50,990 --> 00:18:52,060
My grades aren't good.

431
00:18:52,711 --> 00:18:53,630
Huixin is number one,

432
00:18:53,777 --> 00:18:54,710
and I'm number five.

433
00:18:54,820 --> 00:18:56,244
There are only four spots available.

434
00:18:56,470 --> 00:18:56,950
Huixin,

435
00:18:57,710 --> 00:18:58,710
the future of pharmacy

436
00:18:58,780 --> 00:18:59,820
depends on you.

437
00:19:02,820 --> 00:19:03,844
Don't talk about me.

438
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:04,580
Li,

439
00:19:04,688 --> 00:19:05,430
what's your plan?

440
00:19:06,630 --> 00:19:07,990
My parents found me a

441
00:19:07,990 --> 00:19:08,955
pharmaceutical company.

442
00:19:09,230 --> 00:19:10,950
Is it Guangfeng?

443
00:19:11,820 --> 00:19:13,300
It's a dream place

444
00:19:13,300 --> 00:19:14,910
for pharmacy graduates.

445
00:19:15,260 --> 00:19:16,020
Their branch

446
00:19:16,100 --> 00:19:17,710
has business with my parents,

447
00:19:17,820 --> 00:19:19,060
so they helped me get in.

448
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:20,950
Don't forget us when you're doing great.

449
00:19:21,630 --> 00:19:22,260
Researchers

450
00:19:22,260 --> 00:19:23,020
depend on you.

451
00:19:23,910 --> 00:19:25,260
Let's raise a toast?

452
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:26,430
Come on.

453
00:19:26,580 --> 00:19:28,430
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

454
00:19:34,190 --> 00:19:35,300
I'll take a call.

455
00:19:40,670 --> 00:19:41,950
Are the exam questions hard?

456
00:19:42,670 --> 00:19:43,500
Not too hard.

457
00:19:43,710 --> 00:19:44,540
Come on, let's drink.

458
00:19:44,870 --> 00:19:45,430
Bottoms up.

459
00:19:45,470 --> 00:19:45,910
Cheers.

460
00:20:05,710 --> 00:20:06,630
Huixin.

461
00:20:07,230 --> 00:20:07,710
Huixin,

462
00:20:07,710 --> 00:20:09,710
what took you so long?

463
00:20:10,020 --> 00:20:10,710
Come here.

464
00:20:10,711 --> 00:20:11,990
Come sit with me for a while.

465
00:20:12,540 --> 00:20:14,020
I haven't had a good chat with you.

466
00:20:17,710 --> 00:20:18,230
Huan'er,

467
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:21,933
do you still want
to go to graduate school?

468
00:20:24,820 --> 00:20:25,430
What's wrong?

469
00:20:27,190 --> 00:20:27,540
I

470
00:20:29,540 --> 00:20:30,910
am not going to graduate school.

471
00:20:32,100 --> 00:20:34,780
I'm going back to my hometown
to look for a job after graduation.

472
00:20:39,870 --> 00:20:40,260
No.

473
00:20:41,260 --> 00:20:43,020
Why do you want
to go back to your hometown?

474
00:20:43,133 --> 00:20:45,100
Isn't it your ambition
to go to graduate school

475
00:20:45,150 --> 00:20:46,500
since you entered university?

476
00:20:46,820 --> 00:20:48,430
You work so hard every day.

477
00:20:48,710 --> 00:20:50,340
You're just giving up like this?

478
00:20:53,755 --> 00:20:55,777
My brother scored very well
in his senior year

479
00:20:55,910 --> 00:20:56,780
of high school.

480
00:20:57,910 --> 00:20:58,740
As an elder sister,

481
00:20:59,820 --> 00:21:00,740
I have to do my part.

482
00:21:01,740 --> 00:21:02,060
No.

483
00:21:02,580 --> 00:21:03,740
What decade are we living in?

484
00:21:03,780 --> 00:21:05,260
Do things like this still happen?

485
00:21:07,740 --> 00:21:08,910
Don't you have a scholarship

486
00:21:08,950 --> 00:21:09,870
and a grant?

487
00:21:09,870 --> 00:21:10,710
You are not dependent

488
00:21:10,710 --> 00:21:11,500
on your family.

489
00:21:11,533 --> 00:21:13,577
How come your family
won't let you study?

490
00:21:14,630 --> 00:21:16,300
My parents called me before.

491
00:21:17,820 --> 00:21:18,710
They're getting old.

492
00:21:19,088 --> 00:21:21,777
They can't afford to support
another university student.

493
00:21:21,777 --> 00:21:23,540
So they want me to go home early

494
00:21:24,580 --> 00:21:25,500
and help out,

495
00:21:25,666 --> 00:21:26,710
and start working early.

496
00:21:28,710 --> 00:21:29,340
Besides,

497
00:21:30,340 --> 00:21:31,470
if I go home early,

498
00:21:31,950 --> 00:21:33,190
I can take care of them

499
00:21:33,340 --> 00:21:34,733
if anything happens to them.

500
00:21:37,260 --> 00:21:38,150
As you know,

501
00:21:39,022 --> 00:21:40,150
I had to repeat a year

502
00:21:40,150 --> 00:21:41,020
to get in here.

503
00:21:41,630 --> 00:21:42,740
Compared to my brother,

504
00:21:43,740 --> 00:21:45,340
I don't have much talent for studying.

505
00:21:59,100 --> 00:21:59,733
Huixin.

506
00:22:11,470 --> 00:22:12,500
I now realize

507
00:22:14,470 --> 00:22:15,950
that studying is the happiest thing

508
00:22:15,990 --> 00:22:17,060
in the world.

509
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,200
There will be one more spot

510
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:27,780
for graduate school if I quit.

511
00:22:30,133 --> 00:22:31,630
If you have made up your mind,

512
00:22:32,390 --> 00:22:34,300
I can help you prepare the documents.

513
00:22:37,060 --> 00:22:37,820
I don't want it.

514
00:22:40,430 --> 00:22:41,340
Consider it

515
00:22:42,150 --> 00:22:43,150
a way to repay you

516
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:46,222
for taking care of me
these past three years.

517
00:22:49,630 --> 00:22:50,260
Huan'er,

518
00:22:53,340 --> 00:22:55,500
actually, I know what you
and the girls did.

519
00:22:58,390 --> 00:22:59,190
Like Li,

520
00:22:59,190 --> 00:23:00,260
she's a rich girl,

521
00:23:01,430 --> 00:23:02,910
but she asked for samples

522
00:23:03,540 --> 00:23:05,150
when she bought things.

523
00:23:08,100 --> 00:23:09,540
Lu is so lazy,

524
00:23:10,177 --> 00:23:11,800
but she always got a part-time job

525
00:23:11,950 --> 00:23:13,430
at the student union.

526
00:23:13,577 --> 00:23:16,244
When she got back to the dorm,
she told me she was going home

527
00:23:16,266 --> 00:23:18,177
and asked me to go in her place.

528
00:23:20,020 --> 00:23:20,630
As for you,

529
00:23:22,022 --> 00:23:23,780
you're afraid I won't
get enough to eat,

530
00:23:24,977 --> 00:23:26,800
so you always buy an extra dish.

531
00:23:28,340 --> 00:23:29,430
No...

532
00:23:32,020 --> 00:23:32,710
Huixin...

533
00:23:35,820 --> 00:23:36,780
Think about it again.

534
00:23:41,100 --> 00:23:41,500
Huixin,

535
00:23:43,060 --> 00:23:44,100
are you alright?

536
00:23:44,500 --> 00:23:45,630
Why are you back?

537
00:23:46,710 --> 00:23:48,020
Qiu Li sent me a message.

538
00:23:51,150 --> 00:23:51,910
Dong Huixin,

539
00:23:52,244 --> 00:23:53,644
are you willing to do that?

540
00:23:55,260 --> 00:23:55,910
Yeah.

541
00:23:56,555 --> 00:23:58,133
You don't get
to choose your background,

542
00:23:58,740 --> 00:24:00,150
but you do get to choose

543
00:24:00,190 --> 00:24:01,630
what kind of life you want to live.

544
00:24:03,230 --> 00:24:05,340
Huixin, even if you don't go
to graduate school,

545
00:24:05,390 --> 00:24:06,820
what can you do back home?

546
00:24:06,866 --> 00:24:08,060
Why don't you stay in Wu'an

547
00:24:08,100 --> 00:24:09,150
and prove yourself?

548
00:24:09,190 --> 00:24:10,540
Yes, just stay.

549
00:24:10,710 --> 00:24:11,950
Think about it.

550
00:24:13,488 --> 00:24:15,222
Give me your parents' phone number.

551
00:24:15,244 --> 00:24:16,066
I'll talk to them.

552
00:24:16,740 --> 00:24:18,150
Stop it.

553
00:24:18,740 --> 00:24:20,540
How do you know if you don't try?

554
00:24:20,580 --> 00:24:21,190
Try it.

555
00:24:21,230 --> 00:24:22,820
You're so young.

556
00:24:24,470 --> 00:24:24,990
Okay.

557
00:24:25,190 --> 00:24:25,950
I'll reconsider.

558
00:24:25,990 --> 00:24:27,022
Let me think about it.

559
00:24:27,340 --> 00:24:28,430
Let me think about it.

560
00:24:28,470 --> 00:24:29,422
Let me think about it.

561
00:24:29,710 --> 00:24:30,820
Stop drinking.

562
00:24:30,910 --> 00:24:31,230
Come on.

563
00:24:31,580 --> 00:24:32,390
We'll drink with you.

564
00:24:32,580 --> 00:24:32,950
Come on.

565
00:24:33,020 --> 00:24:34,288
- Qiu Li, get down.
- Qiu Li.

566
00:24:34,311 --> 00:24:35,644
- Qiu Li.
- Let's drink.

567
00:24:36,580 --> 00:24:37,230
Let's drink.

568
00:24:38,820 --> 00:24:39,470
You girls...

569
00:24:40,500 --> 00:24:41,100
Cheers!

570
00:24:41,630 --> 00:24:42,540
Don't go back.

571
00:24:42,580 --> 00:24:43,740
Don't go back.

572
00:24:44,060 --> 00:24:45,340
Forget the unhappy things.

573
00:24:46,470 --> 00:24:47,870
Let's drink. Come on, cheers!

574
00:24:47,950 --> 00:24:48,390
Cheers!

575
00:24:53,740 --> 00:24:54,540
Huixin.

576
00:24:55,710 --> 00:24:56,740
Huixin.

577
00:25:01,230 --> 00:25:03,100
